<br>
Nobody is stoping anyone from being able to worship in school. What is often put to a stop is public presentations of that worship. Why? Because not everyone is a believer in the particular faith put on exhibition.<br>
<br>
Also, we can't do what we want to at all times. In fact, some religions require animal sacrafice (Santoria, for example) and they can't just slaughter a chicken at school while praying.<br>
<br>
<i>"If students want to take their lunch hour to group with friends and pray then they should be able to."</i><br>
<br>
Agreed.<br>
<br>
<i>"Now Joe and Sally Muslim are offended cause they don’t want to hear the Christians pray. So they write their congressman, senator and president to tell them. The government, applying socialism to the event, pass a law forbidding anyone to pray in that room ever solely because it was not fair to everyone...BS! And that is basically what we have today in the public schools."</i><br>
<br>
It's not bullshit. It is common sense. The Christians, in your example, don't want to hear the Muslims' prayers to Allah any more than the Muslims want to hear them! Laws are passed forbidding vocalized prayer in the classroom in order to protect each and every person in the classroom. Again, I sure the hell don't want my children having to hear some small minded person vocalize a prayer. Yes, they are small minded, because if they were "big enough" they would know and understand that their god can hear whispers just as well. The only reason why they pray aloud is because of arrogance.<br>
<br>
<i>"I’m not really sure why you are so hostile towards "little minded" Christians while so open minded towards other religions..? Is it an underdog thing?"</i><br>
<br>
I apologise. I am not really hostile towards any religion. I am not very toleratant of the arrogance of many Christians (since I mostly run into their doctrines and way of life trying to encroach upon my liberties). A Christian who has to force thier way of life upon others is small minded. Rheaton, you have given me no indication you are such a person. I do apologise for offending you, though.<br>
